radioSystem.name: radioSystem

revisions.description: MIB version 01.00.05 - added radioXpd in radioStatusTable - deprecated linkXpd in linkStatusTable
MIB version 01.00.04 - Added linkXpd to linkStatusTable - changed MAX-ACCESS clause of linkChRadioSettingsIdx from read-only to read-create - Fixed DESCRIPTION of linkSettingsTable

MIB version 01.00.03 - Added linkConfigurationInProgress and linkConfigurationInProgressTrapNotification - Added radio radioRxBerThresholdTable - Added fadeMarginMeasure - Deprecated linkFadeMarginMeasure - Added table radioLoopCapabilityTable - Added table sspTable - Added table stm1BulkSettingsTable - Added table linkE1vsSTM1CapacityTable - Deprecated linkAcmMaxTDMCapacity - Deprecated linkTfcTable, linkProTable and linkProMaintTable. - Added linkTfcV2Table, linkProV2Table and linkProMaintV2Table in order to replace deprecated tables. - Added channelSpacingSelection
Removed alarmTrapNumber from TRAPs and IMPORTS.

MIB version 01.00.02 Changes for support of modulation 4096QAM: - DESCRIPTION of linkBandwidthAndModulation - ModulationMap TEXTUAL-CONVENTION - BitsPerSymbol TEXTUAL-CONVENTION Changes for support of channel spacing 60MHz and 80MHz: - DESCRIPTION of linkBandwidthAndModulation - ChannelSpacing TEXTUAL-CONVENTION

MIB version 01.00.01 - Added combinedRadioCapabilitiesTable, combinedRadioFrequencyTable, combinedRadioDuplexFrequencyTable and combinedRadioPowerScalingTable - Declared deprecated linkCapabilitiesTable, linkFrequencyTable, linkDuplexFrequencyTable, linkAcmPowerScaling, linkAcmAtpcRxPowerScaling and linkAcmPowerRange. - Added linkNotMatchingRadiosAlarm and linkNotMatchingRadiosAlarmSeverityCode

ChannelSpacing.name: ChannelSpacing
ChannelSpacing.description: This TC describes a data type which identifies a RF channel spacing.

ModulationMap.name: ModulationMap
ModulationMap.description: This data type is used as the syntax of the radioBranchModulationMap and radioBranchRefModulationMap objects.

ConfigMismatchReason.name: ConfigMismatchReason
ConfigMismatchReason.description: This data type is used to specify the cause of Config Mismatch Alarm, that is the mismatch between the radio link capability and the current local and remote configuration. - securityMismatch(0) Copyright violation - frequencyFailMismatch(1) Configured frequency is out of Filter-Bandwidth - frequencyAlertMismatch(2) Configured frequency across Filter-Bandwidth - ptxMismatch(3) Tx power configured incongruent with RF Tx power limits - channelSpacingAndModulationMismatch(4) Bandwidth and/or modulation configured is invalid (RF doesn't support it) - remoteConfigurationMismatch(5) Incongruence between the couple of Terminal Radio Unit (TRU) in the link: - Frequency Incongruent (Freq) - Reference Bandwidth and Modulation incongruent - Acm-Tx map in congruent with remote Acm-Rx map - acmMismatch(6) Obsolete (no longer used) - profileSetMismatch(7) The selected profile set is not supported by the TRU

RadioCapability.name: RadioCapability
RadioCapability.description: This data type is used as the syntax of the radioBranchKeyFeatures objects.

BitsPerSymbol.name: BitsPerSymbol
BitsPerSymbol.description: his TC describes a data type which identifies a RF channel spacing.

Stm1IndexOrZero.name: Stm1IndexOrZero
Stm1IndexOrZero.description: This textual convention permits the additional value of zero to an stm1Index in stm1Table. The value zero is object-specific and must therefore be defined as part of the description of any object which uses this syntax. Examples of the usage of zero might include situations where stm-1 was unknown, or when none or all stm-1s need to be referenced.

radioSystemMibVersion.name: radioSystemMibVersion
radioSystemMibVersion.description: Numerical version of this module. The string version of this MIB have the following format: XX.YY.ZZ so, for example, the value 1 should be interpreted as 00.00.01 and the value 10001 should be interpreted as 01.00.01.

radioTable.name: radioTable
radioTable.description: A list of radio interface entries. This table is useful to show the manager all the available radio interfaces on the equipment. Moreover it is a reference for Performance Monitoring (PWR and G828).

radioEntry.name: radioEntry
radioEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular radio interface.

radioIndex.name: radioIndex
radioIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each radio interface. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1.

radioLabel.name: radioLabel
radioLabel.description: A textual string containing information about the radio interface. This string should include the name of the manufacturer, the product name and the version of the interface hardware/software.

radioIfIndex.name: radioIfIndex
radioIfIndex.description: This object defines a greater than zero value to identify an interface in ifTable or a zero value if ifTable is not supported.

radioStorageType.name: radioStorageType
radioStorageType.description: The storage type of this conceptual row. Conceptual rows having the value 'permanent' need not allow write-access to any columnar objects in the row.

xpicTable.name: xpicTable
xpicTable.description: A list of xpic radio interface entries. If a manager wants to make an xpic link, it should only add a particular xpic radio interface to an xpic link.

xpicEntry.name: xpicEntry
xpicEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular xpic radio interface.

xpicIndex.name: xpicIndex
xpicIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each xpic radio interface. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1.

xpicRadioIdx.name: xpicRadioIdx
xpicRadioIdx.description: Index of xpic radio interface, corresponding to an available xpic radio interface in radioTable.

xpicRowstatus.name: xpicRowstatus
xpicRowstatus.description: Status of this conceptual row in xpicTable.

xpicChTable.name: xpicChTable
xpicChTable.description: A list of xpic channel entries. This table maps each xpic radio in respective xpic radio interface.

xpicChEntry.name: xpicChEntry
xpicChEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular xpic channel. It defines radio interface and polarization for a given xpic channel.

xpicChPolIndex.name: xpicChPolIndex
xpicChPolIndex.description: This object identifies the xpic radio polarization.

xpicChRadioIdx.name: xpicChRadioIdx
xpicChRadioIdx.description: Xpic radio interface, corresponding to a radio interface in radioTable, used to make up the given xpic radio interface.

xpicChRowstatus.name: xpicChRowstatus
xpicChRowstatus.description: Status of this conceptual row in xpicChTable.

linkAvailableIndex.name: linkAvailableIndex
linkAvailableIndex.description: Shows an index which is available for creation of a new link in the system. It shows the smallest available index. Any attempt to create a link with a different index results in a failure.

linkEntry.name: linkEntry
linkEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular link.

linkIndex.name: linkIndex
linkIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each link. Manager must use the first available index, suggested by linkAvailableIndex.

linkType.name: linkType
linkType.description: This object identifies link type. Supported link types are: single link, 1+1 Hot Standby, 1+1 Frequency Diversity, 2+0 XPIC, 2+2 XPIC Hot Standby, 2+2 XPIC Frequency Diversity and N+1.

linkLabel.name: linkLabel
linkLabel.description: A textual string containing information about the link. This string should give more details about link specific parameters.

linkIfIndex.name: linkIfIndex
linkIfIndex.description: This object defines a greater than zero value to identify a link in ifTable or a zero value if ifTable is not supported.

linkRowstatus.name: linkRowstatus
linkRowstatus.description: Status of this row of linkTable. This object is used to manage the creation and deletion of conceptual rows in linkTable. To create a row in this table, a manager should set rowstatus to createAndWait(5) and choose a link type. Respective entries in linkSettingsTable, linkStatusTable and tdmSettingsTable will be created by agent.In case of protection links proper entries in linkProtectionTable will be also created. Until instances of all corresponding columns are appropriately configured, the value of the corresponding instance of rowstatus is notReady(3). When there is sufficient information to (attempt to) make the conceptual row available for use by the managed device, then the rowstatus column turns into notInService(2); manager must set rowstatus to active(1) to make the conceptual row active. The contents of linkSettingsTable and radioSettingsTable can be changed only if this object is notInService(2).

linkChTable.name: linkChTable
linkChTable.description: A list of link channel entries.

linkChEntry.name: linkChEntry
linkChEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular link channel.

linkChRadioIdx.name: linkChRadioIdx
linkChRadioIdx.description: Radio channel index that corresponds to an available radio interface in radioTable.

linkChRadioSettingsIdx.name: linkChRadioSettingsIdx
linkChRadioSettingsIdx.description: Radio Settings Index. This object is a foreign key for a corresponding radioSettingsTable entry, which is automatically created by agent.

linkChRowstatus.name: linkChRowstatus
linkChRowstatus.description: Status of this row of linkChTable. This object is used to manage the creation and deletion of conceptual rows in linkChTable. To create a row in this table, a manager should set rowstatus to createAndWait(5). Until instances of all corresponding columns are appropriately configured, the value of the corresponding instance of rowstatus is notReady(3). When there is sufficient information to (attempt to) make the conceptual row available for use by the managed device, then the rowstatus column turns into notInService(2); manager must set rowstatus to active(1) to make the conceptual row active. The content of radioSettingsTable can be changed only if this object is notInService(2).

linkSettingsTable.name: linkSettingsTable
linkSettingsTable.description: Table with link settings entries. This table contains all parameters of a radio frequency link. The content of this table can be changed by a manager if linkRowStatus is notInService(2).

linkBandwidthAndModulation.name: linkBandwidthAndModulation
linkBandwidthAndModulation.description: Link Modulation and Bandwidth (channel spacing). The value of this object value is computed by: 65536*modulation+bandwidth where bandwidth selection is: 0 = 3.5Mhz 1 = 7MHz 2 = 14MHz 3 = 28MHz 4 = 56MHz 5 = 10MHz 6 = 20MHz 7 = 30MHz 8 = 40MHz 9 = 50MHz 10 = 112Mhz 11 = 250Mhz 12 = 500Mhz 13 = 750Mhz 14 = 1Ghz 15 = 60MHz 16 = 80MHz and modulation is in bit-per-symbol: 1 = BPSK 2 = 4QAM 3 = 8PSK 4 = 16QAM 5 = 32QAM 6 = 64QAM 7 = 128QAM 8 = 256QAM 9 = 512QAM 10 = 1024QAM 11 = 2048QAM. 12 = 4096QAM. Examples: 250Mhz-4QAM (131083), 500Mhz-4QAM (131084), 250Mhz-16QAM (262155), 500Mhz-64QAM (393228). Note: 0 bit-per-symbol is not possible, so value 0 is used for BandwidthAndModulation unassigned.

linkAcmEngineEnable.name: linkAcmEngineEnable
linkAcmEngineEnable.description: This object is used to enable/disable the ACM engine

linkTxUpperProfile.name: linkTxUpperProfile
linkTxUpperProfile.description: The object (and linkTxLowerProfile object) is used to restrict the TX profile range when ACM is enabled.

linkTxLowerProfile.name: linkTxLowerProfile
linkTxLowerProfile.description: The object (and linkTxUpperProfile object) is used to restrict the TX profile range when ACM is enabled.

linkTxPwrThresh.name: linkTxPwrThresh
linkTxPwrThresh.description: Threshold (value +3 , +15 dB) relative to nominal value of the TX power below wich the related alarm is set.

linkRxPwrThresh.name: linkRxPwrThresh
linkRxPwrThresh.description: Threshold (value -40 , -99 dBm) for RX power below wich the related alarm is set.

linkProfilesSetSelection.name: linkProfilesSetSelection
linkProfilesSetSelection.description: Selection of the working profile set between high gain (max robustness) profile set and high throughput (max capacity) profile set. The set of profiles high gain features a greater robustness against to the set of profiles high throughput. For radio systems that do not have more sets of profiles, this object becomes read only and its reading shows the only one set of profiles supported.

linkXpicControlProcedure.name: linkXpicControlProcedure
linkXpicControlProcedure.description: Set by manager to enable\disable XPIC alarm control procedure. Only for XPIC configurations.

radioSettingsTable.name: radioSettingsTable
radioSettingsTable.description: Table with radio settings entries. This table contains all parameters of a radio terminal. The content of this table can be changed only linkRowStatus is notInService(2)

radioSettingsLabel.name: radioSettingsLabel
radioSettingsLabel.description: A textual string containing information about the radio interface.

radioTxFrequency.name: radioTxFrequency
radioTxFrequency.description: Transmitted frequency in KHz. Null value means invalid frequency.

radioDuplexFrequency.name: radioDuplexFrequency
radioDuplexFrequency.description: Value of duplex frequency in KHz. -2 means not set.

radioTxAttenuation.name: radioTxAttenuation
radioTxAttenuation.description: Transmitter attenuation relative to nominal power (dBm).

radioAtpcPwrHigh.name: radioAtpcPwrHigh
radioAtpcPwrHigh.description: ATPC Control - Local Rx Power High (dBm range -30 to -80) -.

radioAtpcPwrLow.name: radioAtpcPwrLow
radioAtpcPwrLow.description: ATPC Control - Local Rx Power Low (dBm range -30 to -80) -.

radioAtpcRange.name: radioAtpcRange
radioAtpcRange.description: Defines the range of the ATPC regulation (expressed in dB) with respect to the current value of maximum Tx output, that is intended as the upper limit of the range. A null value means no limit: the lower limit of the range is equal to minimum Ptx.

tdmSettingsEntry.name: tdmSettingsEntry
tdmSettingsEntry.description: An entry containing tdm parameters for a particular link.

tdmE1Channel.name: tdmE1Channel
tdmE1Channel.description: Number of E1 channels. This object is used to define the capacity of E1 tributaries assigned to a given radio link. The capacity is changed in steps of E1 (2Mbit/s).

tdmE1Framer.name: tdmE1Framer
tdmE1Framer.description: This object is used to attach the framer to a given E1.

radioCapabilitiesTable.name: radioCapabilitiesTable
radioCapabilitiesTable.description: Table with RadioCapabilities entries: there is an entry for each radioTable rows.

radioCapabilitiesCapability.name: radioCapabilitiesCapability
radioCapabilitiesCapability.description: Bit map to describe the radio features.

radioCapabilitiesTxMinFrequency.name: radioCapabilitiesTxMinFrequency
radioCapabilitiesTxMinFrequency.description: Minimum of available channel frequency in KHz.

radioCapabilitiesTxMaxFrequency.name: radioCapabilitiesTxMaxFrequency
radioCapabilitiesTxMaxFrequency.description: Maximum of available channel frequency in KHz.

radioCapabilitiesExtendedMinPwr.name: radioCapabilitiesExtendedMinPwr
radioCapabilitiesExtendedMinPwr.description: Minimum extended Ptx power for fade margin.

radioStatusTable.name: radioStatusTable
radioStatusTable.description: Table with RadioStatus records: one record for 1+0 configuration and two record for 1+1 configuration.

radioCurrentDuplexFrequency.name: radioCurrentDuplexFrequency
radioCurrentDuplexFrequency.description: Spacing between transmitted and received frequency in KHz.

radioTxChannelSpacing.name: radioTxChannelSpacing
radioTxChannelSpacing.description: Half of transmitted signal channel spacing in KHz.

radioNormalizedMse.name: radioNormalizedMse
radioNormalizedMse.description: Normalized MSE (Mean Squared Error) is an indicator of the Signal to Noise (S/N) ratio. It's in 0.1 dB steps

radioRxActiveStatus.name: radioRxActiveStatus

radioTxActiveStatus.name: radioTxActiveStatus
radioTxActiveStatus.description: Transmitter Active status with associated Severity. In 1+1 Hot Standby radio system, only one TX is active. TXs are active in other configurations of the radio system.

radioCableOpenAlarm.name: radioCableOpenAlarm
radioCableOpenAlarm.description: Cable connnecting ODU is open: alarm status with associated severity.

radioCableShortAlarm.name: radioCableShortAlarm
radioCableShortAlarm.description: Cable connnecting ODU is in short-circuit: alarm status with associated severity.

radioInvalidFrequencyAlarm.name: radioInvalidFrequencyAlarm
radioInvalidFrequencyAlarm.description: Invalid frequency alarm with associated severity.

radioBaseBandRxAlarm.name: radioBaseBandRxAlarm
radioBaseBandRxAlarm.description: Base Band Rx alarm status with associated severity.

radioModulatorFailAlarm.name: radioModulatorFailAlarm
radioModulatorFailAlarm.description: Modulator Fail Alarm status with associated severity.

radioDemodulatorFailAlarm.name: radioDemodulatorFailAlarm
radioDemodulatorFailAlarm.description: Demodulator Fail Alarm status with associated severity.

radioRxPowerLowAlarm.name: radioRxPowerLowAlarm
radioRxPowerLowAlarm.description: Receiver power low alarm status with associated severity.

radioTxPowerLowAlarm.name: radioTxPowerLowAlarm
radioTxPowerLowAlarm.description: Transmitter power low alarm status with associated severity.

radioRemDemodulatorFailAlarm.name: radioRemDemodulatorFailAlarm
radioRemDemodulatorFailAlarm.description: Remote Demodulator Fail Alarm status with associated severity.

radioVcoFailAlarm.name: radioVcoFailAlarm
radioVcoFailAlarm.description: RT VCO fail alarm status with associated severity.

radioRxIFAgcAlarm.name: radioRxIFAgcAlarm

radioTxIFAgcAlarm.description: RT Tx IF AGC fail alarm status with associated severity.

radioIduOduCommunicationAlarm.name: radioIduOduCommunicationAlarm
radioIduOduCommunicationAlarm.description: Communication from IDU towards ODU is down

radioOduIduCommunicationAlarm.name: radioOduIduCommunicationAlarm
radioOduIduCommunicationAlarm.description: Communication from ODU towards IDU is down

radioLocalOduAlarmSynthesis.name: radioLocalOduAlarmSynthesis
radioLocalOduAlarmSynthesis.description: Local ODU alarm synthesis with associated severity.

radioRemoteOduAlarmSynthesis.name: radioRemoteOduAlarmSynthesis
radioRemoteOduAlarmSynthesis.description: Local ODU alarm synthesis alarm status with associated severity.

radioConfigMismatchAlarm.name: radioConfigMismatchAlarm
radioConfigMismatchAlarm.description: Config Mismatch alarm status with associated severity and related map.

radioConfigAlarmReason.name: radioConfigAlarmReason
radioConfigAlarmReason.description: Bit map to describe the Config Mismatch Alarm

radioRxQualityLowAlarm.name: radioRxQualityLowAlarm
radioRxQualityLowAlarm.description: High BER Alarm status with associated severity.

radioRxQualityWarningAlarm.name: radioRxQualityWarningAlarm
radioRxQualityWarningAlarm.description: The RX signal is close to cause errors on payload.

radioXpd.name: radioXpd
radioXpd.description: Cross-Polarization Discrimination, in tenths of dB, is the difference between the received signal power of the co-polarized main beam, and it componemt received on the cross-polarized signal. This object shows an extimated value of the XPD performed by the cross-polarization interference canceller (XPIC). This means that the measure is reliable if: - XPIC is on (linkType is radio2p0Xpic(4), or radio2p2XpicHS(5), or radio2p2XpicFD(6)) - Alarm radioDemodulatorFailAlarm is cleared. - XPD is not too high, since without cross-polar interference the canceller is not able to works well. Basically, in this condition, the extimated XPD is greater than the real one.

radioMaintTable.name: radioMaintTable
radioMaintTable.description: Table with Command for maintenance of radio branch. Objects in this table is not persistent. An Instance of this table is created on creation of radioBranchEntry

radioTxStatus.name: radioTxStatus
radioTxStatus.description: Transmitter status control. The value transmitterOff(1) is related to a manual operation. The value permanentOff(3) is persistent across restart.

radioRFLoopTestResult.name: radioRFLoopTestResult
radioRFLoopTestResult.description: Radio branch RT loop test result.

radioRFLoopTestPercTime.name: radioRFLoopTestPercTime
radioRFLoopTestPercTime.description: Radio branch RT loop test time percentage

radioRtPsuOff.name: radioRtPsuOff
radioRtPsuOff.description: It switches on/off the Rt power supply

radioLom.name: radioLom
radioLom.description: It is used to enable the IP packet forwarding towards Radio.

radioXpic.name: radioXpic
radioXpic.description: Enable of the cross polarization interference cancellation of this radio. The value disable is tied to a manual operation (ManOpRecord). This object is applicable only if thiis radio belongs to a 2+0 XPIC or 2+2 XPIC link.

radioFrequencyTable.name: radioFrequencyTable
radioFrequencyTable.description: Availables channels for selected channel spacing and modulation (see leaf radioFreqTableSelection).

radioDuplexFrequencyTable.name: radioDuplexFrequencyTable
radioDuplexFrequencyTable.description: Table with available duplex frequencies. Duplex frequency is the absolute value of difference between RX and TX frequency.

radioDuplexFreqEntry.name: radioDuplexFreqEntry
radioDuplexFreqEntry.description: Duplex Frequency entry. There is an entry for each available duplex frequency.

radioModulationTable.name: radioModulationTable
radioModulationTable.description: List of modulations related to channel spacing.

radioChannelSpacing.name: radioChannelSpacing
radioChannelSpacing.description: This object identifies the channel spacing.

radioModulationMap.name: radioModulationMap
radioModulationMap.description: List of modulations in the radioChanSpacing

radioRefModulationMap.name: radioRefModulationMap
radioRefModulationMap.description: List of modulations that can be selected as reference in the radioChanSpacingId

linkPolIndex.name: linkPolIndex
linkPolIndex.description: This object identifies the radio polarization. In XPIC radio link identifies one of the polarizations.

linkAcmRxProfile.name: linkAcmRxProfile
linkAcmRxProfile.description: This object reports the ACM profile number in use in the radio Rx. It is the linkAcmProfileId of linkAcmTable. Label is linkAcmProfileLabel from linkAcmTable

linkAcmTxProfile.name: linkAcmTxProfile
linkAcmTxProfile.description: This object reports the ACM profile number in use in the radio Tx. It is the linkAcmProfileId of linkAcmTable. Label is linkAcmProfileLabel from linkAcmTable

linkAcmRxProfileLabel.name: linkAcmRxProfileLabel
linkAcmRxProfileLabel.description: ASCII string used to describe current acm rx profile

linkAcmTxProfileLabel.name: linkAcmTxProfileLabel
linkAcmTxProfileLabel.description: ASCII string used to describe current acm tx profile

linkAcmRxModulation.name: linkAcmRxModulation
linkAcmRxModulation.description: This object is the type of modulation of the Rx profile in use.

linkAcmTxModulation.name: linkAcmTxModulation
linkAcmTxModulation.description: This object is the type of modulation of the Tx profile in use.

linkAcmRxCode.name: linkAcmRxCode
linkAcmRxCode.description: This object is the type of codificator of the Rx profile in use.

linkAcmTxCode.name: linkAcmTxCode
linkAcmTxCode.description: This object is the type of codificator of the Tx profile in use.

linkTxETHCapacity.name: linkTxETHCapacity
linkTxETHCapacity.description: This object reports (in Kbits/sec) the transmitted payload capacity used by the Ethernet

linkRxETHCapacity.name: linkRxETHCapacity
linkRxETHCapacity.description: This object reports (in Kbits/sec) the received payload capacity used by the Ethernet

linkTxTDMCapacity.name: linkTxTDMCapacity

linkRxTDMCapacity.name: linkRxTDMCapacity

linkRescueModulation.name: linkRescueModulation
linkRescueModulation.description: This object is the modulation used when the remote terminal is unreachable, ie traffic on radio link is down.

linkReducedCapacityAlarm.name: linkReducedCapacityAlarm

linkLinkTelemetryFailAlarm.name: linkLinkTelemetryFailAlarm

linkIdMismatchAlarm.name: linkIdMismatchAlarm

linkXpicProcedureBlockAlarm.name: linkXpicProcedureBlockAlarm

linkXpicRemTxOffAlarm.name: linkXpicRemTxOffAlarm

linkRemoteIduAlarmSynthesis.description: Synthesis of the remote IDU alarms

linkNotMatchingRadiosAlarm.name: linkNotMatchingRadiosAlarm
linkNotMatchingRadiosAlarm.description: Radios of the link does not have matched parameters.

linkConfigurationInProgress.name: linkConfigurationInProgress
linkConfigurationInProgress.description: The link is being configured and the table linkSettingsTable is not available for modifying parameters.

This object shows an extimated value of the XPD performed by the cross-polarization interference canceller (XPIC). This means that the measure is reliable if: - XPIC is on (linkType is radio2p0Xpic(4), or radio2p2XpicHS(5), or radio2p2XpicFD(6)) - Alarm radioDemodulatorFailAlarm is cleared. - XPD is not too high, since without cross-polar interference the canceller is not able to works well. linkTfcTable.name: linkTfcTable
linkTfcTable.description: Transmitter Fail Check feature. In 1+1 HS configuration, the radio terminal that doesn't receive signals on both receivers, requests the remote transmitter switch. This table was deprecated and replaced by linkTfcV2Table. It is a view of the rows of the linkTfcV2Table with the same linkIndex and linkPolIndex equal to 1, in order to ensure compatibility with old SNMP managers.

linkTfcAction.name: linkTfcAction
linkTfcAction.description: reset: to clear the forced switch generated by Trasmission Fail Check algorithm (only if 1+1 configuration and ISO system).

linkTfcControl.name: linkTfcControl
linkTfcControl.description: It enables the Tx switch from remote equipment (only if 1+1 configuration and ISO system).

linkTfcWatchWindow.name: linkTfcWatchWindow
linkTfcWatchWindow.description: Watch Window (in seconds) related to Trasmission Fail Check algorithm (only if 1+1 configuration and ISO system).

linkTfcAlarmThreshold.name: linkTfcAlarmThreshold

linkTfcAlarm.name: linkTfcAlarm
linkTfcAlarm.description: Transmission switch alarm generated by Trasmission Fail Check algorithm (only if 1+1 configuration and ISO system).

linkTfcRowStatus.name: linkTfcRowStatus
linkTfcRowStatus.description: Status of this conceptual row in linkTfcTable.

linkMaintTable.name: linkMaintTable
linkMaintTable.description: Table with commands for maintenance of radio link. Objects in this table is not persistent. An Instance of this table is created on creation of linkStatusEntry

linkBerStart.name: linkBerStart
linkBerStart.description: Stop, Start (resetting errors and counters) the pattern. This item is linked to a manual operation (ManOpRecord) instance.

linkBaseBandLom.name: linkBaseBandLom
linkBaseBandLom.description: It is used to enable the IP packet forwarding towards modems. This item is linked to a manual operation (ManOpRecord) instance.

linkFadeMarginMeasure.name: linkFadeMarginMeasure
linkFadeMarginMeasure.description: Set by manager to start/stop fade margin measure. This item is linked to a manual operation (ManOpRecord) instance. This object is deprecated and replaced by fadeMarginMeasure.

linkXpicControlProcedureReset.name: linkXpicControlProcedureReset
linkXpicControlProcedureReset.description: Set by manager to reset the XPIC control procedure after a blocking action.

linkBerTable.name: linkBerTable
linkBerTable.description: Table with Command to estimate BER of radio equipment. Every objects in this table is not persistent. An Instance of this table is created on creation of linkStatusEntry

linkBerErrorCounterH.name: linkBerErrorCounterH
linkBerErrorCounterH.description: High 32 bit part of the 64 bit error counter. Bit 32-63.

linkBerErrorCounterL.name: linkBerErrorCounterL
linkBerErrorCounterL.description: Low 32 bit part of the 64 bit error counter. Bit 0-31.

linkBerDataCounterH.name: linkBerDataCounterH
linkBerDataCounterH.description: High 32 bit part of the 64 bit data counter. Bit 32-63.

linkBerDataCounterL.name: linkBerDataCounterL
linkBerDataCounterL.description: Low 32 bit part of the 64 bit data counter. Bit 0-31.

linkAcmProfileId.name: linkAcmProfileId
linkAcmProfileId.description: This object identifies the profile number for the radio selected by the object linkAcmId.

linkAcmProfileModulation.name: linkAcmProfileModulation
linkAcmProfileModulation.description: This object is the modulation of the profile.

linkAcmProfileCode.name: linkAcmProfileCode
linkAcmProfileCode.description: This object is the type of codificator of the profile.

linkAcmProfileCapacity.name: linkAcmProfileCapacity
linkAcmProfileCapacity.description: This object is used to contain total capacity of profile (in kbits/sec).

linkAcmProfileLabel.name: linkAcmProfileLabel
linkAcmProfileLabel.description: ASCII string used to assign a name to profile.

linkAcmProfileEnable.name: linkAcmProfileEnable
linkAcmProfileEnable.description: The object is used to contain if the use of this profile is enabled or disabled

linkAcmMaxTDMCapacity.name: linkAcmMaxTDMCapacity
linkAcmMaxTDMCapacity.description: This object reports the maximum capacity that can be assigned to the TDM traffic. The capacity is specified in number of E1 (2Mbit/s). This object has been superseded by linkE1vsSTM1CapacityTable.

linkAcmPowerScaling.name: linkAcmPowerScaling
linkAcmPowerScaling.description: This object contains the difference (in eighth of dB) between the TX power at this profile modulation and the TX power at the reference modulation. The power scaling value is achieved from the table linkPtxProfileTable. This object is deprecated: see combinedRadioPowerScalingTable.

linkAcmDownshiftThreshold.name: linkAcmDownshiftThreshold
linkAcmDownshiftThreshold.description: The object is used to contain the downshift threshold in dB/10.

linkAcmUpshiftThreshold.name: linkAcmUpshiftThreshold
linkAcmUpshiftThreshold.description: The object is used to contain the upshift threshold in dB/10.

linkAcmActiveProfile.name: linkAcmActiveProfile
linkAcmActiveProfile.description: This object is used to contain the active status of this profile. The value of the object is related to linkAcmRxProfile and linkAcmTxProfile of the LinkStatusEntry.

linkAcmTDMCapacity.name: linkAcmTDMCapacity
linkAcmTDMCapacity.description: This object reports current TDM capacity (in kbits/sec) of the profile.

linkAcmETHCapacity.name: linkAcmETHCapacity
linkAcmETHCapacity.description: This object reports current ETH capacity (in Kbits/sec) of the profile.

linkAcmAtpcRxPowerScaling.name: linkAcmAtpcRxPowerScaling
linkAcmAtpcRxPowerScaling.description: This object contains the difference (in eighth of dB) between the ATPC RX level thresholds at this profile modulation and the ATPC RX level thresholds at the upper modulation. This object is deprecated: see combinedRadioPowerScalingTable.

linkAcmPowerRange.name: linkAcmPowerRange
linkAcmPowerRange.description: This object contains (in dB) the current value of ATPC range. This object is deprecated: see combinedRadioPowerScalingTable.

linkProTable.name: linkProTable
linkProTable.description: A list of protection link entries. This table was deprecated and replaced by linkProV2Table. It is a view of the rows of the linkProV2Table with the same linkIndex and linkPolIndex equal to 1, in order to ensure compatibility with old SNMP managers

linkProEntry.name: linkProEntry
linkProEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a protected link.

linkProProtectionTxChIdx.name: linkProProtectionTxChIdx
linkProProtectionTxChIdx.description: This object identifies the tx protection channel of a protected link. This object is not applicable in case of not-revertive protection. For N+1 links a value different from zero must be set.

linkProProtectionRxChIdx.name: linkProProtectionRxChIdx
linkProProtectionRxChIdx.description: This object identifies the rx protection channel of a protected link. This object is not applicable in case of not-revertive protection. For N+1 links a value different from zero must be set.

linkProTxWtrTime.name: linkProTxWtrTime
linkProTxWtrTime.description: It defines the Wait Time (in minutes) to Restore in transmission when revertive protection is enabled. Zero value means no switch. If switch is not supported or protection is not revertive, a value different from zero cannot be set.

linkProRxWtrTime.name: linkProRxWtrTime
linkProRxWtrTime.description: It defines the Wait Time (in minutes) to Restore in reception when revertive protection is enabled. Zero value means no switch. If switch is not supported or protection is not revertive, a value different from zero cannot be set.

linkProTxSwitchedChIdx.name: linkProTxSwitchedChIdx
linkProTxSwitchedChIdx.description: This object reports the index of tx channel switched to protection. This object is applicable only for N+1 protection schema.

linkProRxSwitchedChIdx.name: linkProRxSwitchedChIdx
linkProRxSwitchedChIdx.description: This object reports the index of rx channel switched to protection. This object is applicable only for N+1 protection schema.

linkProTxRevertive.name: linkProTxRevertive
linkProTxRevertive.description: It defines if tx protection is revertive or not revertive. In case of N+1 protection, protection is always revertive.

linkProRxRevertive.name: linkProRxRevertive
linkProRxRevertive.description: It defines if rx protection is revertive or not revertive. In case of N+1 protection, protection is always revertive.

linkProExtraTraffic.name: linkProExtraTraffic
linkProExtraTraffic.description: This object enables or disables the transfer of extra traffic on the protection channel in a N+1 link. This object must be set to disabled in case of architectures different for N+1.

linkProRowStatus.name: linkProRowStatus
linkProRowStatus.description: Status of this conceptual row in linkProTable.

linkProMaintTable.name: linkProMaintTable
linkProMaintTable.description: A list of maintenance commands for protected links. A row in this table is added on creation of a row in linkProTable. This table was deprecated and replaced by linkProMaintV2Table. It is a view of the rows of the linkProMaintV2Table with the same linkIndex and linkPolIndex equal to 1, in order to ensure compatibility with old SNMP managers

linkProMaintEntry.name: linkProMaintEntry
linkProMaintEntry.description: An entry containing maintenance commands applicable to a protected link.

linkProMaintTxLockout.name: linkProMaintTxLockout
linkProMaintTxLockout.description: Command to enable/disable tx lockout. This object is applicable only in case of N+1 protections.

linkProMaintRxLockout.name: linkProMaintRxLockout
linkProMaintRxLockout.description: Command to enable/disable rx lockout. This object is applicable only in case of N+1 protections.

linkProMaintTxForced.name: linkProMaintTxForced
linkProMaintTxForced.description: Command to force switch to a given transmission channel. Zero value means no switch.

linkProMaintRxForced.name: linkProMaintRxForced
linkProMaintRxForced.description: Command to force switch to a given receiving channel. Zero value means no switch.

linkProMaintTxWtrReset.name: linkProMaintTxWtrReset
linkProMaintTxWtrReset.description: Clear wait time to restore making the revertive path immediately available.

linkProMaintRxWtrReset.name: linkProMaintRxWtrReset
linkProMaintRxWtrReset.description: Clear wait time to restore making the revertive path immediately available.

linkCapabilitiesTable.name: linkCapabilitiesTable
linkCapabilitiesTable.description: Table with RadioCapabilities entries: there is an entry for each linkTable row. In 1+1 HS and XPIC radio links, this table contains only values supported by both radios. In 1+1 FD radio link, managers have to know the capabilities of each channel. As such, this table is declared deprecated and replaced by combinedRadioCapabilitiesTable.

linkCapabilitiesCapability.name: linkCapabilitiesCapability
linkCapabilitiesCapability.description: Bit map to describe the radio features.

linkCapabilitiesTxMinFrequency.name: linkCapabilitiesTxMinFrequency
linkCapabilitiesTxMinFrequency.description: Minimum of available channel frequency in KHz.

linkCapabilitiesTxMaxFrequency.name: linkCapabilitiesTxMaxFrequency
linkCapabilitiesTxMaxFrequency.description: Maximum of available channel frequency in KHz.

linkCapabilitiesExtendedMinPwr.name: linkCapabilitiesExtendedMinPwr
linkCapabilitiesExtendedMinPwr.description: Minimum extended Ptx power for fade margin.

linkFrequencyTable.name: linkFrequencyTable
linkFrequencyTable.description: Availables channels for selected channel spacing and modulation In 1+1 HS and XPIC radio links, this table contains only values supported by both radios. In 1+1 FD radio link, managers have to know the allowable frequencies of each channel. As such, this table is declared deprecated and replaced by combinedRadioFrequencyTable.

linkDuplexFrequencyTable.name: linkDuplexFrequencyTable
linkDuplexFrequencyTable.description: Table with available duplex frequencies. Duplex frequency is the absolute value of difference between RX and TX frequency. In 1+1 HS and XPIC radio links, this table contains only values supported by both radios. In 1+1 FD radio link, managers have to know the allowable duplex frequencies of each channel. As such, this table is declared deprecated and replaced by combinedRadioDuplexFrequencyTable.

linkDuplexFreqEntry.name: linkDuplexFreqEntry
linkDuplexFreqEntry.description: Duplex Frequency entry. For each available duplex frequency

linkModulationTable.name: linkModulationTable
linkModulationTable.description: List of modulation related to channel spacing. In 1+1 HS and XPIC radio links, this table contains only values supported by both radios.

linkChannelSpacing.name: linkChannelSpacing
linkChannelSpacing.description: This object identifies the channel spacing.

linkModulationMap.name: linkModulationMap
linkModulationMap.description: List of modulation in the linkChanSpacing

linkRefModulationMap.name: linkRefModulationMap
linkRefModulationMap.description: List of modulations that can be selected as reference in the linkChanSpacingId

combinedRadioCapabilitiesTable.name: combinedRadioCapabilitiesTable
combinedRadioCapabilitiesTable.description: Table with RadioCapabilities entries: there is an entry for each radioSettingTable row. In 1+1 HS and XPIC radio links, this table contains only values supported by both radios belonging to the link. In 1+1 FD radio link, managers have to know the allowable duplex frequencies of each channel. As such, this table is declared deprecated and replaced by combinedRadioCapabilitiesTable.

combinedRadioCapabilitiesCapability.name: combinedRadioCapabilitiesCapability
combinedRadioCapabilitiesCapability.description: Bit map to describe the radio features.

combinedRadioCapabilitiesTxMinFrequency.name: combinedRadioCapabilitiesTxMinFrequency
combinedRadioCapabilitiesTxMinFrequency.description: Minimum of available channel frequency in KHz.

combinedRadioCapabilitiesTxMaxFrequency.name: combinedRadioCapabilitiesTxMaxFrequency
combinedRadioCapabilitiesTxMaxFrequency.description: Maximum of available channel frequency in KHz.

combinedRadioCapabilitiesExtendedMinPwr.name: combinedRadioCapabilitiesExtendedMinPwr
combinedRadioCapabilitiesExtendedMinPwr.description: Minimum extended Ptx power for fade margin.

combinedRadioFrequencyTable.name: combinedRadioFrequencyTable
combinedRadioFrequencyTable.description: Availables channels for selected channel spacing and modulation In 1+1 HS and XPIC radio links, this table contains only values supported by both radios.

combinedRadioDuplexFrequencyTable.name: combinedRadioDuplexFrequencyTable
combinedRadioDuplexFrequencyTable.description: Table with available duplex frequencies. Duplex frequency is the absolute value of difference between RX and TX frequency. In 1+1 HS and XPIC radio links, this table contains only values supported by both radios.

combinedRadioDuplexFreqEntry.name: combinedRadioDuplexFreqEntry
combinedRadioDuplexFreqEntry.description: Duplex Frequency entry. There is an entry for each available duplex frequency.

combinedRadioPowerScalingTable.name: combinedRadioPowerScalingTable
combinedRadioPowerScalingTable.description: List of modulation related to channel spacing. In 1+1 HS and XPIC radio links, this table contains only values supported by both radios.

combinedRadioPowerScaling.name: combinedRadioPowerScaling
combinedRadioPowerScaling.description: This object contains the difference (in eighth of dB) between the TX power at this profile modulation and the TX power at the reference modulation. The power scaling value is achieved from the table linkPtxProfileTable.

combinedRadioAtpcRxPowerScaling.name: combinedRadioAtpcRxPowerScaling
combinedRadioAtpcRxPowerScaling.description: This object contains the difference (in eighth of dB) between the ATPC RX level thresholds at this profile modulation and the ATPC RX level thresholds at the upper modulation.

combinedRadioPowerRange.name: combinedRadioPowerRange
combinedRadioPowerRange.description: This object contains (in dB) the current value of ATPC range.

stm1BulkMappingTable.name: stm1BulkMappingTable
stm1BulkMappingTable.description: Table with entries containing stm-1 bulk transport parameters for a particular link. For each link are present as many rows as the STM-1 that the link can carry in bulk mode.

stm1BulkChanIndex.name: stm1BulkChanIndex
stm1BulkChanIndex.description: STM-1 channel index. The range of this object is from 1 to N, where N is the number of STM-1 that a link can carry in bulk mode.

stm1BulkChannel.name: stm1BulkChannel
stm1BulkChannel.description: Index of the stm-1 in stm1Table. The SNMP agent will accept only index of a STM-1 present in stm1Table with stm1Structure set to opaque(4).

linkE1vsSTM1CapacityTable.name: linkE1vsSTM1CapacityTable
linkE1vsSTM1CapacityTable.description: Table with entries containing the E1 cpacity according to the tributaries STM-1 configured to be carried in bulk mode.

linkE1vsSTM1CapacityStm1.name: linkE1vsSTM1CapacityStm1
linkE1vsSTM1CapacityStm1.description: Number of tributaries STM-1 configured to be transported in bulk mode.

linkE1vsSTM1CapacityE1.name: linkE1vsSTM1CapacityE1
linkE1vsSTM1CapacityE1.description: Number of E1 that can be carried by this profile according to the the tributaries STM-1 carried in bulk mode.

linkTfcV2Table.name: linkTfcV2Table
linkTfcV2Table.description: Transmitter Fail Check feature. In 1+1 HS configuration, the radio terminal that doesn't receive signals on both receivers, requests the remote transmitter switch.

linkTfcV2Action.name: linkTfcV2Action
linkTfcV2Action.description: reset: to clear the forced switch generated by Trasmission Fail Check algorithm (only if 1+1 configuration and ISO system).

linkTfcV2Control.name: linkTfcV2Control
linkTfcV2Control.description: It enables the Tx switch from remote equipment (only if 1+1 configuration and ISO system).

linkTfcV2WatchWindow.name: linkTfcV2WatchWindow
linkTfcV2WatchWindow.description: Watch Window (in seconds) related to Trasmission Fail Check algorithm (only if 1+1 configuration and ISO system).

linkTfcV2AlarmThreshold.name: linkTfcV2AlarmThreshold
linkTfcV2AlarmThreshold.description: Alarm Threshold (number of seconds with both remote RX in fail) related to Trasmission Fail Check algorithm (only if 1+1 configuration and ISO system).

linkTfcV2Alarm.name: linkTfcV2Alarm
linkTfcV2Alarm.description: Transmission switch alarm generated by Trasmission Fail Check algorithm (only if 1+1 configuration and ISO system).

linkTfcV2RowStatus.name: linkTfcV2RowStatus
linkTfcV2RowStatus.description: Status of this conceptual row in linkTfcV2Table.

linkProV2Table.name: linkProV2Table
linkProV2Table.description: A list of protection link entries.

linkProV2Entry.name: linkProV2Entry
linkProV2Entry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a protected link.

linkProV2ProtectionTxChIdx.name: linkProV2ProtectionTxChIdx
linkProV2ProtectionTxChIdx.description: This object identifies the tx protection channel of a protected link. This object is not applicable in case of not-revertive protection. For N+1 links a value different from zero must be set.

linkProV2ProtectionRxChIdx.name: linkProV2ProtectionRxChIdx
linkProV2ProtectionRxChIdx.description: This object identifies the rx protection channel of a protected link. This object is not applicable in case of not-revertive protection. For N+1 links a value different from zero must be set.

linkProV2TxWtrTime.name: linkProV2TxWtrTime
linkProV2TxWtrTime.description: It defines the Wait Time (in minutes) to Restore in transmission when revertive protection is enabled. Zero value means no switch. If switch is not supported or protection is not revertive, a value different from zero cannot be set.

linkProV2RxWtrTime.name: linkProV2RxWtrTime
linkProV2RxWtrTime.description: It defines the Wait Time (in minutes) to Restore in reception when revertive protection is enabled. Zero value means no switch. If switch is not supported or protection is not revertive, a value different from zero cannot be set.

linkProV2TxSwitchedChIdx.name: linkProV2TxSwitchedChIdx
linkProV2TxSwitchedChIdx.description: This object reports the index of tx channel switched to protection. This object is applicable only for N+1 protection schema.

linkProV2RxSwitchedChIdx.name: linkProV2RxSwitchedChIdx
linkProV2RxSwitchedChIdx.description: This object reports the index of rx channel switched to protection. This object is applicable only for N+1 protection schema.

linkProV2TxRevertive.name: linkProV2TxRevertive
linkProV2TxRevertive.description: It defines if tx protection is revertive or not revertive. In case of N+1 protection, protection is always revertive.

linkProV2RxRevertive.name: linkProV2RxRevertive
linkProV2RxRevertive.description: It defines if rx protection is revertive or not revertive. In case of N+1 protection, protection is always revertive.

linkProV2ExtraTraffic.name: linkProV2ExtraTraffic
linkProV2ExtraTraffic.description: This object enables or disables the transfer of extra traffic on the protection channel in a N+1 link. This object must be set to disabled in case of architectures different for N+1.

linkProV2RowStatus.name: linkProV2RowStatus
linkProV2RowStatus.description: Status of this conceptual row in linkProV2Table.

linkProMaintV2Table.name: linkProMaintV2Table
linkProMaintV2Table.description: A list of maintenance commands for protected links. A row in this table is added on creation of a row in linkProV2Table.

linkProMaintV2Entry.name: linkProMaintV2Entry
linkProMaintV2Entry.description: An entry containing maintenance commands applicable to a protected link.

linkProMaintV2TxLockout.name: linkProMaintV2TxLockout
linkProMaintV2TxLockout.description: Command to enable/disable tx lockout. This object is applicable only in case of N+1 protections.

linkProMaintV2RxLockout.name: linkProMaintV2RxLockout
linkProMaintV2RxLockout.description: Command to enable/disable rx lockout. This object is applicable only in case of N+1 protections.

linkProMaintV2TxForced.name: linkProMaintV2TxForced
linkProMaintV2TxForced.description: Command to force switch to a given transmission channel. Zero value means no switch.

linkProMaintV2RxForced.name: linkProMaintV2RxForced
linkProMaintV2RxForced.description: Command to force switch to a given receiving channel. Zero value means no switch.

linkProMaintV2TxWtrReset.name: linkProMaintV2TxWtrReset
linkProMaintV2TxWtrReset.description: Clear wait time to restore making the revertive path immediately available.

linkProMaintV2RxWtrReset.name: linkProMaintV2RxWtrReset
linkProMaintV2RxWtrReset.description: Clear wait time to restore making the revertive path immediately available.

sspTable.name: sspTable
sspTable.description: A list of operative and administrative set of parameters. This table holds three row for every link (and its polarizations) configured in the NE: 1) administative parameters of local NE 2) operative parameters of local NE 3) administative parameters of remote NE

sspEntry.name: sspEntry
sspEntry.description: An entry containing SSP relevant parameters.

sspParameterType.name: sspParameterType
sspParameterType.description: This object identifies what parameters are for.

sspLinkAcmEngineEnable.name: sspLinkAcmEngineEnable
sspLinkAcmEngineEnable.description: This object is used to enable/disable the ACM engine.

sspLinkTxUpperProfile.name: sspLinkTxUpperProfile
sspLinkTxUpperProfile.description: The object (and linkTxLowerProfile object) is used to restrict the TX profile range when ACM is enabled.

sspLinkTxLowerProfile.name: sspLinkTxLowerProfile
sspLinkTxLowerProfile.description: The object (and linkTxUpperProfile object) is used to restrict the TX profile range when ACM is enabled.

sspLinkProfilesSetSelection.name: sspLinkProfilesSetSelection
sspLinkProfilesSetSelection.description: Selection of the working profile set between high gain (max robustness) profile set and high throughput (max capacity) profile set. The set of profiles high gain features a greater robustness against to the set of profiles high throughput. For radio systems that do not have more sets of profiles, this object becomes read only and its reading shows the only one set of profiles supported.

sspTdmE1Channel.name: sspTdmE1Channel
sspTdmE1Channel.description: Number of E1 channels. This object is used to define the capacity of E1 tributaries assigned to a given radio link. The capacity is changed in steps of E1 (2Mbit/s).

sspTdmStm1Channel.name: sspTdmStm1Channel
sspTdmStm1Channel.description: Number of STM-1 channels transported in bulk mode.

radioLoopCapabilityTable.name: radioLoopCapabilityTable
radioLoopCapabilityTable.description: This table shows which group a radio loop belongs to. Radios with the same group number (identifier) close loop simultaneously.

radioLoopCapabilityEntry.name: radioLoopCapabilityEntry
radioLoopCapabilityEntry.description: An entry containing a group identifier for each radio loop type.

radioLoopRfGroup.name: radioLoopRfGroup
radioLoopRfGroup.description: The group to which the radio RF loop belong to.

radioLoopIqGroup.name: radioLoopIqGroup
radioLoopIqGroup.description: The group to which the radio IQ loop belong to.

radioLoopBaseBandGroup.name: radioLoopBaseBandGroup
radioLoopBaseBandGroup.description: The group to which the radio base loop belong to.

radioRxBerThresholdTable.name: radioRxBerThresholdTable
radioRxBerThresholdTable.description: This table shows the nominal and measured values of RX power at a bit error rate (BER) equal to 10e-6.

radioRxBerThresholdEntry.name: radioRxBerThresholdEntry
radioRxBerThresholdEntry.description: An entry containing the RX power thresholds.

radioRxBerThresholdStatus.name: radioRxBerThresholdStatus
radioRxBerThresholdStatus.description: This object shows whether the following objects are significant.

radioNominalRxBerThreshold.name: radioNominalRxBerThreshold
radioNominalRxBerThreshold.description: The nominal value of RX power @ BER equal to 10e-6

radioMeasuredRxBerThreshold.name: radioMeasuredRxBerThreshold
radioMeasuredRxBerThreshold.description: The measured value of RX power @ BER equal to 10e-6.

radioRemDemodulatorFailAlarmSeverityCode.name: radioRemDemodulatorFailAlarmSeverityCode
radioRemDemodulatorFailAlarmSeverityCode.description: Defines the severity associated to the radioRemDemodulatorFailAlarm and enables/disables the trap generation on status change event.

radioRxActiveStatusTrapNotification.name: radioRxActiveStatusTrapNotification
radioRxActiveStatusTrapNotification.description: Enable/disables (statusTrapEnable or statusTrapDisable) the trap generation on status change event for radioRxActivestatus

radioTxActiveStatusTrapNotification.name: radioTxActiveStatusTrapNotification
radioTxActiveStatusTrapNotification.description: Define the severity associated to the radioTxActivestatus and enable/disable the trap generation on status change event.

radioCableOpenAlarmSeverityCode.name: radioCableOpenAlarmSeverityCode
radioCableOpenAlarmSeverityCode.description: Defines the severity associated to the radioCableOpen and enables/disables the trap generation on status change event.

radioCableShortAlarmSeverityCode.name: radioCableShortAlarmSeverityCode
radioCableShortAlarmSeverityCode.description: Defines the severity associated to the radioCableShort and enables/disables the trap generation on status change event.

radioInvalidFrequencyAlarmSeverityCode.name: radioInvalidFrequencyAlarmSeverityCode
radioInvalidFrequencyAlarmSeverityCode.description: Defines the severity associated to the radioInvalidFrequencyAlarm and enables/disables the trap generation on status change event.

radioBaseBandRxAlarmSeverityCode.name: radioBaseBandRxAlarmSeverityCode
radioBaseBandRxAlarmSeverityCode.description: Defines the severity associated to the radioBaseBandRxAlarm and enables/disables the trap generation on status change event.

radioModulatorFailAlarmSeverityCode.name: radioModulatorFailAlarmSeverityCode
radioModulatorFailAlarmSeverityCode.description: Defines the severity associated to the radioModulatorFailAlarm and enables/disables the trap generation on status change event.

radioDemodulatorFailAlarmSeverityCode.name: radioDemodulatorFailAlarmSeverityCode
radioDemodulatorFailAlarmSeverityCode.description: Defines the severity associated to the radioDemodulatorFailAlarm and enables/disables the trap generation on status change event.

radioRxPowerLowAlarmSeverityCode.name: radioRxPowerLowAlarmSeverityCode
radioRxPowerLowAlarmSeverityCode.description: Defines the severity associated to the radioRxPowerLowAlarm and enables/disables the trap generation on status change event.

radioTxPowerLowAlarmSeverityCode.name: radioTxPowerLowAlarmSeverityCode
radioTxPowerLowAlarmSeverityCode.description: Defines the severity associated to the radioTxPowerLowAlarm and enables/disables the trap generation on status change event.

radioVcoFailAlarmSeverityCode.name: radioVcoFailAlarmSeverityCode
radioVcoFailAlarmSeverityCode.description: Defines the severity associated to the radioVcoFailAlarm and enables/disables the trap generation on status change event.

radioRxIFAgcAlarmSeverityCode.name: radioRxIFAgcAlarmSeverityCode
radioRxIFAgcAlarmSeverityCode.description: Defines the severity associated to the radioRxIFAgcAlarm and enables/disables the trap generation on status change event.

radioTxIFAgcAlarmSeverityCode.name: radioTxIFAgcAlarmSeverityCode
radioTxIFAgcAlarmSeverityCode.description: Defines the severity associated to the radioTxIFAgcAlarm and enables/disables the trap generation on status change event.

radioIduOduCommunicationAlarmSeverityCod.name: radioIduOduCommunicationAlarmSeverityCode
radioIduOduCommunicationAlarmSeverityCod.description: Define the severity associated to the radioIduOduCommunicationAlarm and enable/disable the trap generation on status change event.

radioOduIduCommunicationAlarmSeverityCod.name: radioOduIduCommunicationAlarmSeverityCode
radioOduIduCommunicationAlarmSeverityCod.description: Define the severity associated to the radioOduIduCommunicationAlarm and enable/disable the trap generation on status change event.

radioLocalOduAlarmSynthesisSeverityCode.name: radioLocalOduAlarmSynthesisSeverityCode
radioLocalOduAlarmSynthesisSeverityCode.description: Define the severity associated to the radioLocalOduAlarmSynthesis and enable/disable the trap generation on status change event.

radioRemoteOduAlarmSynthesisSeverityCode.name: radioRemoteOduAlarmSynthesisSeverityCode
radioRemoteOduAlarmSynthesisSeverityCode.description: Define the severity associated to the radioRemoteOduAlarmSynthesis and enable/disable the trap generation on status change event.

radioConfigMismatchAlarmSeverityCode.name: radioConfigMismatchAlarmSeverityCode
radioConfigMismatchAlarmSeverityCode.description: Defines the severity associated to the radioConfigMismatchAlarm and enables/disables the trap generation on status change event.

radioPrxHysteresisValue.name: radioPrxHysteresisValue
radioPrxHysteresisValue.description: Defines the delta value associated to the radioPrx before having a new trap generation (radioPtxChange TRAP). The zero value is not allowed.

radioPtxHysteresisValue.name: radioPtxHysteresisValue
radioPtxHysteresisValue.description: Defines the delta value associated to the radioPtx before having a new trap generation (radioPtxChange TRAP). The zero value is not allowed.

radioPrxHysteresisValueTrapNotification.name: radioPrxHysteresisValueTrapNotification
radioPrxHysteresisValueTrapNotification.description: Enables/disables the Rx change trap generation on status change event.

radioPtxHysteresisValueTrapNotification.name: radioPtxHysteresisValueTrapNotification
radioPtxHysteresisValueTrapNotification.description: Enables/disables the Tx change trap generation on status change event.

radioRxQualityLowAlarmSeverityCode.name: radioRxQualityLowAlarmSeverityCode
radioRxQualityLowAlarmSeverityCode.description: Define the severity associated to the radioRxQualityLowAlarm and enable/disable the trap generation on status change event.

radioRxQualityWarningAlarmSeverityCode.name: radioRxQualityWarningAlarmSeverityCode
radioRxQualityWarningAlarmSeverityCode.description: Define the severity associated to the radioRxQualityWarningAlarm and enable/disable the trap generation on status change event.

linkReducedCapacityAlarmSeverityCode.name: linkReducedCapacityAlarmSeverityCode
linkReducedCapacityAlarmSeverityCode.description: Define the severity associated to the linkReducedCapacityAlarm and enable/disable the trap generation on status change event.

linkLinkTelemetryFailAlarmSeverityCode.name: linkLinkTelemetryFailAlarmSeverityCode
linkLinkTelemetryFailAlarmSeverityCode.description: Define the severity associated to the linkLinkTelemetryFailAlarm and enable/disable the trap generation on status change event.

linkIdMismatchAlarmSeverityCode.name: linkIdMismatchAlarmSeverityCode
linkIdMismatchAlarmSeverityCode.description: Define the severity associated to the linkIdMismatchAlarm and enable/disable the trap generation on status change event.

linkRadioEocAlarmSeverityCode.name: linkRadioEocAlarmSeverityCode
linkRadioEocAlarmSeverityCode.description: Define the severity associated to the linkRadioEocAlarm and enable/disable the trap generation on status change event.

linkSetupMismatchAlarmSeverityCode.name: linkSetupMismatchAlarmSeverityCode
